  "prompt": "What are some animals native to New Zealand?",
  "response": "New Zealand has a unique and diverse array of fauna. Some notable animals native to New Zealand include:\n\n1. **Kiwi** - A small, flightless bird that is an iconic symbol of New Zealand. There are several species, including the North Island brown kiwi and the little spotted kiwi.\n\n2. **K\u0101k\u0101p\u014d** - A large, nocturnal, flightless parrot known for its distinctive moss-green feathers and critically endangered status.\n\n3. **Tuatara** - A reptile that resembles a lizard but belongs to a distinct lineage dating back to the time of the dinosaurs.\n\n4. **Kea** - A highly intelligent alpine parrot known for its playful behavior and curiosity.\n\n5. **T\u016b\u012b** - A native bird with iridescent plumage and unique vocalizations, including whistles, clicks, and squawks.\n\n6. **Moa** - Extinct flightless birds that were once native to New Zealand; they included several species varying in size.\n\n7. **New Zealand Falcon (K\u0101rearea)** - A bird of prey known for its agility and hunting prowess.\n\n8. **Hector's Dolphin** - One of the smallest and rarest marine dolphins, found predominantly around the South Island.\n\n9. **New Zealand Fur Seal (Kekeno)** - A marine mammal that can often be spotted along the country's rocky shores.\n\n10. **Pukeko** - A swamp bird with striking blue and purple feathers and long red legs.\n\nThese animals contribute to the rich biodiversity of New Zealand and many of them are unique to the country due to its geographic isolation.",
